// @test regression/INV034-for-body-wrap-indent
// @description CE10161: a complete counted-for header followed by a wrap-continuation line (body indent not a multiple of 4) glues into the header and breaks the statement. 4-multiple bodies and genuinely wrapped headers stay clean. Probed 2026-06-05, see INV034.
// @expects parse: fail
// @expects error: line=4, message=/Incorrect .for. statement. Expecting .to <expression>./

//@version=6
indicator("INV034")
s = 0.0
for i = 1 to 7
     s := s + close[i]
for j = 1 to 7
    s := s + close[j]
for k = 1 to
     7
    s := s + close[k]
plot(s)
